msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

# 7c50e9e97e4d4884bf7724d03671664e
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_crashlog.en.rst:33
msgid ""
":program:`traffic_crashlog` is a helper process that catches Traffic "
"Server crashes and writes a crash report log to the logging directory. "
"Other than for debugging or development purposes, "
":program:`traffic_crashlog` is not intended for users to run directly."
msgstr ""

# 0bb4070310c44345ae8c1edbbdd9fab0
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_crashlog.en.rst:38
msgid ""
"When :ref:`traffic_server` starts, it will launch a "
":program:`traffic_crashlog` process and keep it stopped, activating it "
"only if a crash occurs."
msgstr ""

# 28527e5adb77425b916a0f694196b35d
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_crashlog.en.rst:42
msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

# 98c9231e306b466e87668e53d2d5377f
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_crashlog.en.rst:48
msgid ""
"This option specifies the host triple for the process that "
":program:`traffic_crashlog` should examine. If a supported host triple is"
" specified, :program:`traffic_crashlog` expects to receive a "
"``siginfo_t`` structure on it's standard input, followed by a "
"``ucontext_t``."
msgstr ""

# 585679e148944a598dda6d8997c3397f
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_crashlog.en.rst:56
msgid ""
"Specifies the process ID of the crashing :program:`traffic_server` "
"process. If this option is not specified, :program:`traffic_crashlog` "
"assumes it should examine it's parent process."
msgstr ""

# f32d2c8936864fc2baa1d4853a6476ff
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_crashlog.en.rst:62
msgid ""
"This option causes :program:`traffic_crashlog` to log the name of the "
"crash log it creates to the system log."
msgstr ""

# 7c0d4bdff5af4c8a83d2c5efbacc41ed
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_crashlog.en.rst:67
msgid ""
"This option enables debugging mode. In this mode, "
":program:`traffic_crashlog` emits the log to it's standard output."
msgstr ""

# 47223a58da7542f4bed3742971553c88
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_crashlog.en.rst:73
msgid ""
"This option causes :program:`traffic_crashlog` to stop itself immediately"
" after it is launched. :program:`traffic_server` will allow it to "
"continue only when a crash occurs."
msgstr ""

# 01d966e620184ba3b095e6f364082f0a
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_crashlog.en.rst:78
msgid "Caveats"
msgstr ""

# f2e91a7cb8ee4552aec1c41ad98c0d67
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_crashlog.en.rst:80
msgid ""
":program:`traffic_crashlog` makes use of various Traffic Server "
"management APIs. If :ref:`traffic_manager` is not available, the crash "
"log will be incomplete."
msgstr ""

# 42ea93332d2c40f89a591016f7ed13bf
#: ../../appendices/command-line/traffic_crashlog.en.rst:84
msgid ""
":program:`traffic_crashlog` may generate a crash log containing "
"information you would rather not share outside your organization. Please "
"examine the crash log carefully before posting it in a public forum."
msgstr ""

